<p>Friday 1st June 1917<br/>Nr Bouzincourt<br/>Reveille 5.30am<br/>Put waggons in line. Breakfast 7am.Cleaning lines and harness cleaning till 12 noon.<br/>2 till 5pm Harness cleaning.<br/>After tea went for a swim in lake about 1 &frac12; mls from our camp. (The first swim I have had since leaving Australia) (but not the first wash).</p>
